# eBook Medium

This class represents a specific Title being offered for sale to Customers in eBook (i.e. "e-reader") format.

◇

subclass_of_key: medium

attributes:
    
    key:
        name: "product key"
        details: |
            Part of Digital Rights Managerment (DRM), which represents the
            eBook medium-spreicfic encryption key for this Title. This is mashed together 
            with a publisher key and given to the Customer so they can unlock and access 
            each legal copy of the Title on the device they bought it for.
        rules: see Engineering Memo PQR789
    
    user_key:
        name: "user key?"
        details: Shows the user key a Custoemr needs to unlock an eBook on their reader.
        derivation: see Engineering Memo PQR789, uses .product key and Title.publisher key via Sold as.


states:

  Exists:
    details: The medium is in the system.

events:

    "«new»":
        details: Create this medium.
        parameters:
            - name: title
              source: somewhere
            - name: isbn
              source: somewhere
            - name: price
              source: somewhere
            - name: cost
              source: somewhere
            - name: media key
              source: somewhere

  
actions:

    Initialize:
        details: Add a new medium to the system.
        requires:
            - |
                ISBN is consistent with the range of Medium.ISBN,
                price is consistent with the range of Medium.selling price,
                cost is consistent with the range of Medium.acquisition cost,
                media key is consistent with the range of .product key
        guarantees:
            - |
                one new eBook Medium exists with:
                    .isbn == isbn,
                    .selling price == price,
                    .acquistion cost == cost,
                    .is visible == false,
                    .product key == media key,
                    this Medium linked to its Title via Sold As

transitions:

    - {from: "", event: "«new»", to: "Exists", action: "Initialize"}